  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Exploring a South Africa Circular Economy Platform</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Large quantities of waste are still landfilled in South Africa, creating harmful emissions. Aside the environmental challenges, inefficient waste management in cities and communities exposes people to a myriad of health risks, establishes high risks of environmental degradation, flooding  (including blocked sewerage systems) and exposes natural resources and water bodies to degradation and reduction in quality. Other factors, including climate change and population growth, will further exacerbate these risks.As a result, despite of a relatively high rate of (informal) solid urban waste recycling, the current economy leads to the depletion of precious resources and does not account for negative externalities exerted upon the environment. A circular economy presents a sustainable solution to part of the socio-economic and environmental challenges resulting from the current linear economic model in South Africa.A circular economy platform can be an important driver connecting government, academia/knowledge institutions and businesses, accelerating and aligning circular economy policy, business and knowledge initiatives in South-Africa.This project identifies the main stakeholders and explores the possibilities of a future circular platform and future circular economy projects.This first phase of preparatory research is to collect information on the set up of a future circular hotspot and to reach commitment within a frontrunners&#x2019; group of stakeholders on the establishment of a South African Circular Economy Platform. And is being implemented by the Africa Circular Economy Network (ACEN)Holland Circular Hotspot aims to provide Dutch technical and other advise and share experiences on the set-up of circular platforms and circular economy.</narrative>
  </description>
